<br>
I don't know if it is the good place to post this but I do it anyway.<br>
<br>
I went to TOFS (Tower of frozen shadow in Velious Iceglad zone ) at lvl 35 and I played with a Cleric (friend of mine in EQ). We were fighting at lvl 1 and 2 of the tower. The tecnique which is quite simple is the cleric cast fear on the mobs. The mobs will than flee to the mirror. Lvl 1 the mobs flee to the entrance mirror. Lvl 2 the mob flee to the mirror that access to lvl 3. Let's be clear when hunting at lvl 1 don't use the right click to select the target or you'll get a zone message and you'll be out of the tower without pet without friends and with some shadow guards taking care of your Hit points (in fact use F8, this works fine). When this part is said. You can nuke fast since the mob will not take care of your aggro until the fear spell worn off (most of the time the mob is dead before). Your pet can even solo one mob alone while siting. At lvl 2 to reach the lvl 3 mirror, use the cleric invis to undead and don't prepare your pet until you get to the mirror. <br>
<br>
Don't use earth pet since root cancel fear.<br>
<br>
To reach the next lvl in this tower you need a key that drop from mobs with name starting with Angry. To get the lvl 3 key for example you have to kill an angry librarian. Not sure for lvl 4 and higher but that's the case for lvl 2 and 3.<br>
<br>
One other point that should be mentionned to be honest 100%, corpse run are deadly since you need a key. So the technique here is to let the guy with the key gate first and the guy that don't have the key suicide himself by taking the maximum aggro. Now I only died two times from bad pull. The risk here is that the mob come by two or tree and the cleric can't cast fear or is resisted. The best bet is two members of the group take the key to lvl 2 and one gate if thing start to feel bad.<br>
<br>
We (Plugdo the cleric and I Mininiu the mage) work our lvl out there. If guild members with lvl 25 to 30 can join us we let them make lvl fast. <br>
<br>
Some info :<br>
<br>
- at lvl 2 with the cleric at lvl 40 and I at lvl 37, I make a bleu per two kills. It is so nice that I can't wait until I come back from XMas vacations. <br>
<br>
- I don't know if it is an exploit but honestly the risk vs exp is so low that I will continue the pratice until LVL 40. At lvl 40 some mobs of the library are green most are bleu. So I think we can do it until lvl 41. If you have a full group with 2 or 3 people of lvl 40 you can risk lvl 3. Be ready for nice corps run. Exp is not bad loot is low but fun is high. We don't have the fear point right now but it should be near a mirror.<br>
<br>
- At lvl 2 you can loot from the ungry librarian the key but also a nice range item that give +3 int +3 wis +15 (or 20 I give this from memory <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) mana and some save vs something. I can't log right now and I am not precise on the object but it is so fine that I was happy jumping right and left when I got it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Manage the aggro, don't be afraid to nuke a mob to let the cleric fear when he has 3 mobs on him. When all mobs are feared, let the cleric med until one fear drop. When the cleric is pulling med. Prepare your pet the best way with armors weapons and all buff, you wont need to recast one.<br>
<br>
Well this is my little clue to make nice exp. Hope you'll test it and enjoy it.<br>
<br>
If you have time and full group go upper, you'll get fun. I eared that lvl 51 makes exp at lvl 7. Some guild friends of lvl 51 already made exp at lvl 3. But the risk there is a bit higher, so don't go if you are not confident in your group.<br>
<br>
Mininiu lvl 37 Mage Arcanes of Norrath guild.<br>
<br>
